#3059
The Cathedral of Our Lady of the All-Night Tool~
You are standing in an ornate chapel, the Cathedral of Our Lady of the
All-Night Tool. A huge set of three stained-glass windows occupy the west wall
of the Cathedral, and a large stained-glass skylight is set into the roof.
An organ is perched on a small balcony set into the east wall, playing soothing
music for all to enjoy.  At the center of the north wall is an altar, which
looks like a large wire spool.  Several items sit atop the altar.  Two
pedestals occupy the east corners, and two more pedestals occupy the west
corners, each containing holy relics for examination.  Also on the northeast
and southwest walls are large tablets containing the 0x10 Commandments.
A large picture hangs over the altar, and two paintings hang on the pedestals
that support the building's roof.  A confessional booth is situated on the
north wall so that sinners might seek absolution for their sins.
~
0 263168 0
E
tablets~
The commandments are as follows:
 
0x0 - I am Athena, thy Goddess. Thou shalt not have false gods before me.
0x1 - Thou shalt not take the name of OnLineConsultant in vain.
0x2 - Thou shalt not eat at Lobdell.
0x3 - Thou shalt keep holy the hour of Star Trek.
0x4 - Honor thy professors, for they are the source of grades.
0x5 - Thou shalt not decrease entropy.
0x6 - Thou shalt not connect PWR to GND.
0x7 - Thou shalt not sex toads.
0x8 - Thou shalt not exceed the speed of light.
0x9 - Keep holy the month of IAP for it is a time of rest.
0xA - IHTFP
0xB - Thou shalt not sleep.
0xC - Thou thalt Consume Caffiene
0xD - Thou shalt not take pass/fail in vain.
0xE - Thou shalt not covet thy neighbor's HP.
0xF - Thou shalt not divide by zero.
~
E
picture~
The picture over the altar is of William Barton Rogers, AKA Saint Rogers.
The left pedestal picture depicts a scene in which an HP 28S is the object
of adoration by reverent geeks; The picture is complete with 1700s clothing
and inscriptions such as "Hackito Egro Sum", "Liberty, Fraternity, Equality,
Caffiene", and "Novus Ordo Seclorum".  The right pedestal picture depicts
a man torn between Athena (complete with helmet, spear, and owl) standing on
a platform inscribed "The Temptation of Six", and another woman standing
on a platform inscribed "The Path of Truth". The background has two winged
terminals flying about.
~
E
pedestals~
On the southeast pedestal sits several guilded monitors, one with it's innards
exposed for all to contemplate. The northeast pedestal contains a vintage
Tektronics 'scope.  The southwest pedestal contains a PDP-8 in a 19-inch
rack, complete with 9-track tape drive and paper-tape reader.  The northwest
pedestal contains a Wang daisy-wheel printer, some disk drivers, random circuit
boards, and magnetic tape.
~
E
altar~
The Altar has a marble top and a vintage 1971 4Kword core memory board inlaid
in it's center. A bottle of Holy Water (Jolt Cola) and a Holy Tome (8.01)
sit on it, and a guilded Macintosh keyboard and some aluminum foil flowers
sit at the base.  The basic shape of the altar resembles and empty wire spool.
Behind the altar sits a donation box, which is a hollowed-out VT-100.
~
E
organ~
The organ plays a medley that starts with Bach's Tocatta and Fugue in D Minor
and continues with many other pieces, including some Gregorian chants. It has
many gold and silver pipes, each tuned to musical perfection. It has a
massive keyboard constructed from 6 computer keyboards, 4 VT-100 keyboards
and two Knight TV keyboards.  The keys have many important messages in them,
such as "Nerd Pride", 37619, IHTFP, "Our Lady of the All-Night Tool", and
3.14159
~
E
skylight~
The skylight radiates with light and color no matter what the weather - It is
illuminated by lights from inside when it is dark or dreary outside.  The
center of the skylight is a logo of a goddess dear to many, an Athena Owl.
Radiating from the owl are 16 pie-shaped wedges, each of which is inscribed
with one of the Many Truths on which our faith is based.  They are, in order:
1: E=MC^2
2: F-> = MA->
3: E = hv
4: PV = nRT
5: e^10 = cosO+i(sin O)
6: e^ix + 1 = 0
7: i^-1 = e^(-(x/2))
8: cos^2O + sin^2(O) = 1
9: de^a/dx | e^adx=e^a
10: |1/xdx = lnz
11: c^2 = a^2 + b^2 - 2ab cosO
12: a = 1/(sqrt)ac
13: VxE-> = aB-> / ai
14: V * B-> = pa ca aE->/ai + paI->
15: V . E-> = caP
16: V . B-> = 0
~
E
windows~
The three stained-glass windows depict three stages in the life of a devout
Tool.  The leftmost shows a common scene is his life; An MIT lecture hall,
complete with students, blackboards, and a professor.  The middle contains
a depiction of a guilded beaver, the holy animal known to walk most closely
with the Englightened Ones. The rightmost window shows a scene of MIT as
seen from Killian Court, complete with Dome and the Tool, standing on a
large stack of unmarked bills so that he might gain entrance to the 'tute.
~
